<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="468" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="11.[1447,2654,1159,2255]" pageId="11" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1450,1795,2023,2056]" pageId="11" pageNumber="468">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Least Concern on The [UCN Red List. Deforestation rates are still low in the geographic distribution of the Whitecollared Titi, and although there is some hunting by indigenous peoples,it does not appear to be a major threat. It is found in Jat National Park.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
